rooms.Name: The begining of Jepoardy Lane.
rooms.Description:
You are standing on a street running east to west in a small suburb. The
houses on the street are neetly designed clones of each other. Each lawn is
carefully manicured. There are dogs barking, and kids playing. Middle aged
suburbanites are washing thier yuppie-mobiles, and tending to their gardens.

Exits.Description: A narrow alleyway heads back to Monroe Street in downtown Chicago.

ExtraDescs.Description:
"Married with Cildren" The Zone.
Created by Xorin on Sept 1, 1996.

This zone is an incomplete replica of the show. I tried to recreate
as much of the show as I could, but that is always impossible. Look carefully
at the descriptions. There are hidden jokes everywhere. There are also over
30 hidden mobs in this zone. Look high, look low.
-Xorin. :)

rooms.Name: On the front lawn of a suburban residence.
rooms.Description:
You stand on the neatly manicured lawn of a suburban resident. As you gaze
around you realize that these people have _way_ too much time. Every blade
of grass is exactly four inches high. The walkway is line by a perfectly
by a single row of flowers. The house is a stndard red brick with an off
white vynil siding, and a black roof. A gleeming blue sedan sits in the
driveway.

rooms.Name: In side a suburban residence.
rooms.Description:
You stant in the livingroom of a suburban home. There is a couch up against
the far wall, sitting opposite a TV. The TV is tuned to Oprah, who is
blabing about how men have destroyed the world. The audience cheers as she
insults men, and all that they do.

rooms.Name: 9764 Jepoardy Lane.
rooms.Description:
As soon as you step off the street onto the lawn, you regret the move. Your
foot lands in somthing squishy. Then there's that horrible stench. The lawn
is not mowed. There is no flower bed. The color of the grass is mostly a pale
brown with the occasional green patch.

rooms.Name: 9766 Jepoardy Lane.
rooms.Description:
Yet another suburban house standt before you. The only difference is that
you swear that you can smell fried chicken. *shrug* Oh well...
There are no kids playing near this house either. There is a mercedes in
the drive. The flower bed in front of the house appears to be frequented
by one of the neighborhood dogs.

rooms.Name: The livingroom of the Bundy residence.
rooms.Description:
You stand in the doorway of the shabby living room. In the middle of the
room is a couch. The middle of the couch has a large round imprint in it.
Around the base of the couch you spy bon-bon crumbs. In front of the couch
is a TV. It is of course tuned to Oprah. Who is tyrading on about men. There
is a stairway leading up stairs, and a kitchen to the north. A close door
leads to the downstairs, and another southwest to the garage. A sliding
glass door leads east to the backyard.

rooms.Name: Al's garage.
rooms.Description:
A thin layer of motor oil covers the floor. There are black tire marks on the
floor. The whole room smells of gassoline, and anti-freeze. Oil cans, and
and rags hang on the wall. A door leads northwest to the livingroom, and
another leads west. The garage door opens to the south.

rooms.Name: The Bundy kitchen.
rooms.Description:
This is the shabby kitchen of the Bundy residence. In the center of the room
is a medium sized table. Along one wall is a cooking range covered in dust.
Next to that, on the north wall is a large brown fridge. Partially dividing
the kitchen and living room is a small counter attached to the east wall.
There is an doorway leading east to the laundry room. Back to the south is
the livingroom.

rooms.Name: Upstairs.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a drab looking hallway. At the north end is a grandfather
clock. To the south is an open door, leading into a bedroom. To the
northwest is a plain brown, closed door. From the other side you here
a hurried scuffling niose. To the north is another closed door. It is
decorated with a colorful AC/DC poster.

rooms.Name: Kelly's room.
rooms.Description:
Pink... Everything is pink... Except of course the navy blue naval uniform on
the floor. The window on the north side has a ladder leaned up against it.
The walls are spotted by chip 'n dale's posters.

rooms.Name: Bud's room.
rooms.Description:
The room is pretty messy. The the floors are covered with clothes. As you
gaze around the room, you notice a piece of flesh colored rubber under the
bed. The walls are covered with several 'girly' posters with such titles as
'Wags. Half girl, half pup'.

rooms.Name: The master bedroom.
rooms.Description:
This is a typical bedroom. There is a large king sized bed in the center of
the room. At the foot of the bed is a TV. On either side of the bed stands
a nightstand. To the west is a door leading to the bedroom. To the east is
an open window overlooking the backyard.

rooms.Name: The upstairs bathroom.
rooms.Description:
This is a small room. A toilet sits in one corner. In the other is a small
shower. There is a sink and mirror along the wall. The sink is covered with
mascara, make-up, and other women's personal items.

rooms.Name: Free falling, SCREAMING, headfirst to your bloody DEATH!
rooms.Description:
Well this sucks... You're falling head first from the window. Amazingly
you still flap your arms and try to fly...

*WHAM*

When you open your eyes, you are floating through the clouds. Everywhere
there are winged people playing harps.  You hear God calling your name from
above. Above you is a bright light...

rooms.Name: On cloud nine.
rooms.Description:
You stand on a cloud in heaven. Below you is the world that you left behind.
You wonder where God gets his shoes. Perhaps you should ask. What kind of
shoes would God wear you wonder...

rooms.Name: The backyard.
rooms.Description:
This is more like Buck's bathroom, than a backyard. The smell is quite  raunchy
out here. Every step you take is into a squishy little pile. Why did you want
to come here anyway?

rooms.Name: The basement.
rooms.Description:
This is a dark, dank, dungeon, of a room. You can hear scurying sounds in
the darkness. The room smells of an old sock. As you walk around the room
are constantly clearing spiderwebs from your path. There is a bed in the
middle of the room. On the north wall is the water heater for the house.

rooms.Name: Al's Bathroom.
rooms.Description:
This is a closet sized bathroom. The walls and the floor are cold, white,
ceramic tile. The whole room says "Step up to the bowl Mister, and make it
a double!"

rooms.Name: Marcy Darcy's livingroom.
rooms.Description:
This is a very neat livingroom. There is a couch in the center of the room.
In front of the couch is a small coffee table. On the coffee table are such
magazines as "Femi-nazi Today" and "Short-Haired Women in Banking." There is
a stairway leading upstairs.

rooms.Name: Upstairs.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a small hallway. To the west is a close door. From the other side
you hear a man chanting "Hit me, beat me, make me bleed! Kinky sex is what I
need!" You can also hear the sharp crack of a bull whip, and what sounds like
scream of a deamon.

rooms.Name: Marcy's bedroom.
rooms.Description:
This is a standard bedroom decorated with many erotic forms of torture. On
the bed are leather straps. The walls are adorned with whips, and scourges.
A pair of shackles are chained to the ceiling. The floor is damp. You don't
want to know why.

rooms.Name: Under the Freeway.
rooms.Description:
You are under a freeway overpass. You peer around under the bridge, and
notice the abode of a local transient. You might be able to climb up onto
the bridge. That is if you really want to be n freeway traffic...

rooms.Name: In to oncoming traffic!!! >>WHAM<<
rooms.Description:
You are standing on the freeway. Looking at the oncomming traffic. OUCH!
That HURT! Maybe you should move before you get hit again. Maybe you
like getting hit by traffic. Either way, you won't last much longer.

rooms.Name: On the freeway.
rooms.Description:
You are standing on a freeway durring rush hour. The cars are bumper to
bumber. The drivers are screaming at each other, and honking their horns.
You are glad that you didn't bring a car.

rooms.Name: Chicago city street.
rooms.Description:
This is your typical downtown street. Trashy. There are bums sleeping every
twenty feet along the sidewalk. There are cars moving up and down the street.
There are bars, and strip joints on every corner. Trash lines the gutters of 
the streets. The whole places smells of smog, and polution.

rooms.Name: In a DEAD END alley.
rooms.Description:
You are standing in a dead end alley. There is trash piled along the walls
of the alley. The walls themselves are covered with profane graffity. As
you stand here you smell the acrid scent of gun smoke. Perhaps you should
leave.

rooms.Name: The Entrance to Troy's.
rooms.Description:
You stand in the entrance way of a male strip joint. There are middle aged
over-weight women crowding the entrance. They push and shove you trying to
catch a glimpse of Zoro. You push your way through the herd, trying to get
inside.

rooms.Name: Before the stage.
rooms.Description:
You stand in a tight space watching the mayhem.There are fat women everywhere.
They are screaming at a buff, male stripper on stage. They are scrambling
up to the stage, fighting to put money in his pants. A smokey haze fills
the room. The noise and thick smoke would drive the average adventurer away.

rooms.Name: On stage.
rooms.Description:
You have managed to make it on stage. The women now begin to screem louder.
Half of them think you are part of the act, and are trying to put money
down your pants. The other half are trying to pull you off stage. The stage
is a runway type stage. It is made of hard wood, and lined with lights, and
small rails. There is a bright hot spotlight shining upon you from above.

rooms.Name: The hallway.
rooms.Description:
You escape the ruckas of the main room. You are standing in a small drab
hallway. The walls are made of cinder blocks. The hall runs from north
to south on the west side of the joint. At the north end of the hall
is a door. On the door is a sign that reads "Troy's Office." You can
hear a voice from the other side of the door.

rooms.Name: Troy's Office
rooms.Description:
You stand in a small dimmly lit office. There is a desk in the middle of the
room. The desk is covered by papers, a coffee mug, and a pencil holder. On the
wall are pictures of all the dancers. As you peer into the corner of the room
you catch a glimpse of movement, but fail to see anything.

rooms.Name: Backstage.
rooms.Description:
You stand backstage of the runway. To the east and west are the dressing rooms
of the dancers. The floor is made of cement, and there are cables hanging
from the ceiling. Who knows what act would use those. You can still hear
the noise of the crowd inside the main room. You can also hear the scurry
of dancers getting ready for an act.

rooms.Name: The dressing room.
rooms.Description:
This is the dressing room for the dancers. SHAME ON YOU! Close your eyes!
There are naked dancers struting around the room. Some are rehersing, others
are primping and doing thier make-up. A few of the dancers glare at you
upon entering the room. But after seeing your weapon, the quickly look away.

rooms.Name: The entrance to the Nudie Bar.
rooms.Description:
You stand in the entrance way of a strip joint. There are middle aged
over-weight men crowding the entrance. They push and shove you trying to
catch a glimpse of hooters. You push your way through the herd, trying to get
inside.

Some of the patrons try to lure the dancer over to them using wads of money.
A spotlight shines down from above on to you and the dancer.

stretch as far as the eye can see. Off in the distance to the north you can 
see the mall. People are swarming all around you, going to and from the mall.
The hot sun beats down upon you. You long for a drin of water.

rooms.Description:
As soon as you walk into this deserted shoe store you regret it. The stench
in horrible. Only a true looser would work in a place like this. There are
gaudy shoes, and purses displayed around the room. There is a dusty register
lying on a counter in one corner.

rooms.Name: A store in the mall.
rooms.Description:
You manage to squeeze into one of the many stores in the mall. All around
